## Project Context & Standards

### 1. Project Overview
- Name: secure_qr_scanner Website
- Objective: Marketing website and privacy policy pages for the QR Scanner app
- Framework: SolidStart (SolidJS with SSR) + TailwindCSS v4
- Design: Purple gradient theme matching the Flutter app
- Purpose: App landing page, privacy policy, terms of service (required for Google Play)

### 2. Code Standards
- Use SolidJS reactive primitives (createSignal, createEffect, etc.)
- Keep components modular and reusable
- Follow SolidStart file-based routing conventions
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Optimize for SEO and fast page loads
- Prefer server-side rendering where appropriate
- Use TailwindCSS v4 utility classes for styling
- Follow the purple gradient design system from app.css

### 3. Design System
- **Purple Gradient Colors:**
  - Primary: #8B5CF6 (violet-500)
  - Secondary: #D946EF (fuchsia-500)
  - Accent: #7C3AED (violet-600)
  - Additional: #A78BFA (violet-400), #E879F9 (fuchsia-400), #C084FC (purple-400)

- **Typography:**
  - Font: Inter (system-ui fallback)
  - Consistent with Flutter app design

- **Theme Support:**
  - Respect `prefers-color-scheme: dark`
  - Provide light and dark mode variants
  - Use CSS custom properties from app.css

### 4. File Structure
- `src/routes/` → Page components (file-based routing)
- `src/components/` → Reusable UI components
- `src/styles/` → Global styles (app.css)
- `public/` → Static assets (images, fonts, etc.)

### 5. SEO & Performance
- Add proper meta tags (title, description, OG tags)
- Optimize images and assets
- Use semantic HTML
- Ensure fast Time to First Byte (TTFB)
- Implement proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3)
- Add structured data where appropriate

### 6. Content Requirements
- Privacy Policy page (required for Google Play)
- Terms of Service page
- App landing/home page
- Clear, user-friendly language
- Mobile-responsive design
- Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA compliance)

### 7. Quality Standards
- No TypeScript errors
- No console warnings in production
- Test on multiple browsers
- Verify responsive design on mobile/tablet/desktop
- Ensure proper SSR hydration
- Check accessibility with screen readers

